<h3 class="postTitle">CAD/Inventor Seminar this Summer</h3>
<div class="date">June 10, 2010</div>
<div class="text"><p>Message from Mark Zach regarding the seminar:</p>
<p>A Computer Aided Design, 3D solid modeling, seminar will be offered again this summer. The seminar will get you started using 3D solid modeling software and will cover everything you need to know to make models of simple parts and assemblies and make drawings of those models. The seminar will introduce the essential solid modeling tools needed to design a large variety of things, such as apparatus for your lab, a table for your living room, or a deck for your backyard. With these basic skills you will be in a good position to use the CAD tools for your design projects and, if you choose, to explore the more advanced features of the software. The seminar will use AutoCAD Inventor and all participants will be able to install AutoCAD Inventor on their own computer (Windows only). An open lab computer will also be available throughout the week.</p>
<p>The group will meet for four one-hour daily sessions in each of two weeks at the times listed below. To get the full benefit of this seminar, you will need to spend at least an hour per day working with the software outside of class. Suggested exercises will be provided. This will be an informal, not-for-credit workshop and all students, faculty and staff are welcome to attend. You may attend all or some of the sessions as your schedule and your interests dictate.</p>
<p>This seminar will be led by Mark Zach, the Instrument Project Manager in the Department of Physics and Astronomy. Mark has over 18 years experience using CAD tools to design industrial equipment, scientific apparatus, furniture, and home remodeling projects. He has also served as a CAD mentor, CAD administrator and has presented numerous times at regional and national CAD user group meetings.</p>
<p>If you are interested, please e-mail <a href="mailto:mzach@carleton.edu">Mark</a> before July 1.</p>
<p>Schedule:<br />
July 12 - 15, 19 - 22<br />
10:00 - 11:00 each day<br />
The location will be determined based on the number of people interested.</p></div>
</div>
</div></div>
